nodes.text: Jizz-wail was a music genre. A quartet performed some jizz-wail in a crowded square in the capital of the planet of Euceron during the Galactic Games of 26 BBY.[source?]
Jizz-wail was briefly mentioned in the 2002 young-readers novel Jedi Quest: The Dangerous Games, written by Jude Watson.

It has an unknown relationship to the musical style known as jizz, featured Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope (1977). The band featured in the cantina scene is performing jizz, an obvious nod to real-world jazz. However, jizz-wail should not be confused with the term "jizz-wailer," which refers to musicians especially adept at performing jizz.
